FTP, SMTP, POP3 and IMAP:
1) FTP:
	You can connect by FTP by typing:
		ftp <ip>
	After that you can type the following as commands:
		USER, PASS, RETR, STOR
		Where RETR is used to get files from an ftp server, and
		STOR is user to upload files to the ftp server.
		You can list the files using (ls) commands
2) SMTP:
	You can send emails using SMTP by typing:
		telnet <IP> 25
	After that you can type the following commands:
		EHLO/HELO - To initiate the smtp session
		MAIL FROM: <email> - Specifies the email sender.
		RCPT TO: <email> - Specifies the email receiver.
		DATA - Indicates the start of the email content.
		. - Indicates the end of the email content.
3) POP3:
	This is used to retrieve emails from a server.
	You can start it by typing:
		telnet <IP> 110
	You then authenticate by typing: USER and PASS.
	You can type: LIST to list all messages and their sizes.
	Then type STAT to get how many messages there are and their total sizes.
	Finally you can type: RETR <message number> to retrieve the actual message
4) IMAP: Synchronizing emails.
	For this, emails are kept on the server and synchronized across the email clients.
	LOGIN <username> <password> authenticates the user
	fetch 4 body[] - This is used to get the fourth message, body and header
